 Manchester City scored three first-half goals against Birmingham City to secure their qualification to the next round of the FA Cup on Sunday afternoon at the Etihad Stadium. Bernando Silva scored a brace in the opening 15 minutes before Phil Folden added to the tally in 33rd minute. The second half witness no more goal as Riyad Mahrez’s goal was properly ruled offside by VAR. Though it was an emphatic display from Pep Guardiola’s men who have already secured a final place berth in the Carabao Cup against Tottenham Hotspur. Post Views: 
